{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"21956c7e-81d2-4162-b625-8fdbc150a8e1","content":"Here's the recommended MSTest setup:\n\n**1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)** — minimal with MSTest.Sdk:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nMSTest.Sdk bundles MSTest runner, assertions, and the test framework — no extra `<PackageReference>` needed.\n\n**2. Enable parallel execution** — add a file called `MyTests.cs` (or any assembly-level location):\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]\n```\n\nThis runs all test methods in parallel by default.\n\n**3. Run database tests sequentially** — use `[DoNotParallelize]` on a class:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Read_After_Write() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\nAny class marked `[DoNotParallelize]` runs its methods sequentially and waits for parallel tests to finish first.\n\n**Summary of key points:**\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---------|-----------|\n| SDK | `MSTest.Sdk/3.7` (no extra packages) |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` |\n| Sequential opt-out | `[DoNotParallelize]` on class |\n| Scope options | `MethodLevel` (max parallelism) or `ClassLevel` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ab5839f9-49e8-4409-bd1c-c1c3cbf8b3f7","outputTokens":418,"requestId":"BD08:2F6EDC:203BB94:24411B5:6A07CEF0"},"id":"cdf46efd-d7e4-400d-a225-fa0d47a6cfe2","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:57:13.903Z","parentId":"f01606a2-1a80-4db0-bd12-a399c345f1f1"}
